                    <head>
                        <title type="uniform" xml:lang="is">Guðmundar saga hin elzta</title>;
                            <origPlace>Iceland</origPlace>, <origDate notBefore="1330" notAfter="1350">c. 1330-1350</origDate>
                        <note>Guðmundar saga in this manuscript (the so-called <q xml:lang="en">oldest saga</q>) is a compilation of the <title type="uniform" xml:lang="is">Prestssaga</title>, <title type="uniform" xml:lang="is">Hrafns saga</title>, <title type="uniform">Íslendinga
                                saga</title>, <title type="uniform" xml:lang="is">Arons saga</title>
                            and annals. AM 399 4to was one of the manuscripts <name type="person" key="PedRes001">Peder Resen</name> presented to the University
                            Library in Copenhagen. This manuscript is one of the few to have
                            survived from this library, which was consumed in the flames of the
                            Great Fire of <name type="place" key="Copen01">Copenhagen</name> in <date when="1728">1728</date>. Luckily, at that time the manuscript was on loan to
                                <name type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name>
                        </note>
                    </head>
